Privacy Policy
Welcome to
glasinfinapps.space Privacy Policy.
Our apps are designed and developed with special attention to your privacy.
Last Updated:
November 12, 2024
glasinfinapps.space may update this Privacy Policy as new features are added or as legal requirements evolve. Unless otherwise specified, changes take effect upon posting. You are encouraged to review the Privacy Policy periodically.
This Privacy Policy outlines how glasinfinapps.space manages and protects your information, including data collected through our website at
www.glasinfinapps.space
("Website") and our mobile applications ("Apps"). Collectively, the Website and Apps are referred to as glasinfinapps.space.
Information Collection and Use
Data We Collect
Non-Personal Information:
When you use our Apps, we collect non-personal information, such as how long the App is used, the screens viewed, and actions taken. This data helps us improve user experience but cannot be used to identify you.
Personal Information:
We do not collect any personal information unless you provide it voluntarily, such as when submitting a support request or subscribing to our newsletter.
Consumption Information:
We collect app usage and other consumptional information. This data can be shared with Apple.
If we receive a refund request for an in-app purchase from an end user, we reserve the right to provide Apple with information regarding the user's in-app purchase consumption. This includes the following data: app usage time, anonymous account identifier, total amount spent, and total amount refunded.
Support Requests
When contacting us for support, you may provide your email address and other relevant details ("Support Information"). This information is used solely to address your inquiries.
Newsletters
If you opt into our optional newsletter, we collect your email address for the sole purpose of sending the newsletter. You can unsubscribe at any time. We do not sell or rent your email address, and it is not combined with other data. Newsletter services may involve third-party providers who are required to use your email address only for fulfilling subscriptions.
Cookies
When you visit our Website, cookies may be sent to your browser to track preferences and enhance your experience. Most browsers allow you to disable cookies or notify you when they are being used. While cookies are not utilized within our Apps, third-party libraries integrated into the Apps may use cookies for their services.
Subscription Terms
If your free trial period ends, you must purchase a subscription to continue using certain features.
Payment is charged to your iTunes Account upon confirmation of purchase.
Subscriptions automatically renew unless auto-renew is disabled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.
You can manage subscriptions and disable auto-renewal via your Account Settings.
Third-Party Links and Services
glasinfinapps.space may include links to third-party websites ("Third-Party Websites") on its Website. These links are provided for convenience, but we are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these websites. Once you leave our Website, this Privacy Policy no longer applies. Use third-party websites at your own risk.
Log Data
If an error occurs during App usage, we may collect device information via third-party tools. This "Log Data" may include:
Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address
Device name and operating system version
App configurations at the time of the error
Timestamp and usage data
This data helps us analyze and resolve issues.
Security
We implement industry-standard practices to safeguard your personal information. However, no method of online transmission or electronic storage is completely secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Privacy of Children
We do not collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided personal information, we delete it securely. Parents and guardians are encouraged to supervise their children's online activities.
Users must be at least 16 years old to consent to data collection, unless parental consent is provided as allowed by local laws.
Policy Updates
We may revise this Privacy Policy over time. Updates will be posted here, and significant changes will be communicated to users.
Contact Us
If you have questions, concerns, or suggestions regarding this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
Email:
support@glasinfinapps.space